Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: A control node for playing an animation once.

Inherits: AnimationNode < Resource < Object

AnimationNodeOneShot

An AnimationNode that plays an animation once.

This node is useful for playing animations that should only run once, such as attacks, jumps, or other one-off actions. It can be configured to control the playback of the animation, including its speed, looping, and whether it should restart when triggered.

Properties:
  - fade_out_time (float): The time in seconds it takes for the animation to fade out after it finishes. Default: 0.0.
  - on_animation_finished (int): Defines what happens when the animation finishes.
    - 0: Continue to next animation.
    - 1: Stop.
    - 2: Reset.
    Default: 0.
  - oneshot (StringName): The name of the animation to play.
  - pause_mode (int): Defines how the animation behaves when the AnimationPlayer is paused.
    - 0: Stop.
    - 1: Pause.
    - 2: Process.
    Default: 1.
  - remaining (float): The remaining time of the animation.
  - reset_on_exit (bool): If true, the animation will reset to its beginning when the node exits. Default: false.
  - start_offset (float): The time in seconds from which to start the animation. Default: 0.0.
  - sync (bool): If true, the animation will synchronize with other animations in the graph. Default: true.

