Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: Describes the AnimationNodeOneShot, an AnimationTree node that executes a sub-animation and returns upon completion, with customizable fade times and filters.

Inherits: AnimationNode<AnimationBaseTag<Resource
This animation node will execute a sub-animation and return once it finishes. Blend times for fading in and out can be customized, as well as filters.

After setting the request and changing the animation playback, the one-shot node automatically clears the request on the next process frame by setting its `request` value to ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_NONE.

GDScript:
# Play child animation connected to "shot" port.
animation_tree.set("parameters/OneShot/request", AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FIRE)
# Alternative syntax (same result as above).
animation_tree["parameters/OneShot/request"] = AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FIRE

# Abort child animation connected to "shot" port.
animation_tree.set("parameters/OneShot/request", AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_ABORT)
# Alternative syntax (same result as above).
animation_tree["parameters/OneShot/request"] = AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_ABORT

# Abort child animation with fading out connected to "shot" port.
animation_tree.set("parameters/OneShot/request", AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FADE_OUT)
# Alternative syntax (same result as above).
animation_tree["parameters/OneShot/request"] = AnimationNodeOneShot.ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FADE_OUT

# Get current state (read-only).
animation_tree.get("parameters/OneShot/active")
# Alternative syntax (same result as above).
animation_tree["parameters/OneShot/active"]

# Get current internal state (read-only).
animation_tree.get("parameters/OneShot/internal_active")
# Alternative syntax (same result as above).
animation_tree["parameters/OneShot/internal_active"]

C#:
# Play child animation connected to "shot" port.
animationTree.Set("parameters/OneShot/request", (int)AnimationNodeOneShot.OneShotRequest.Fire);

# Abort child animation connected to "shot" port.
animationTree.Set("parameters/OneShot/request", (int)AnimationNodeOneShot.OneShotRequest.Abort);

# Abort child animation with fading out connected to "shot" port.
animationTree.Set("parameters/OneShot/request", (int)AnimationNodeOneShot.OneShotRequest.FadeOut);

# Get current state (read-only).
animationTree.Get("parameters/OneShot/active");

# Get current internal state (read-only).
animationTree.Get("parameters/OneShot/internal_active");
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: This document describes the AnimationNodeOneShot class, which is used to play an animation once and then transition to another animation.

Inherits: AnimationNode < AnimationRootNode < Resource

Description:
Plays an animation once and then transitions to another animation.

Properties:
- `animation` (String): The name of the animation to play.
- `delay` (float): The delay before playing the animation. Default: 0.0.
- `fade_out` (float): The duration of the fade-out after the animation finishes. Default: 0.0.
- `mix_mode` (MixMode): The mix mode to use when blending animations. Default: 0.
- `one_shot` (bool): If true, the animation will only play once. If false, it will loop. Default: true.
- `sync` (bool): If true, the animation will sync with the parent animation. Default: true.

Methods:
- `_get_animation_process_mode()` → AnimationRootNode.AnimationProcessMode: Returns the animation process mode.
- `_set_animation_process_mode(mode: AnimationRootNode.AnimationProcessMode)`: Sets the animation process mode.
- `get_animation()` → String: Returns the name of the animation to play.
- `set_animation(anim: String)`: Sets the name of the animation to play.

Enums:
- MixMode:
    - MIX_DEFAULT (0): Default mix mode.
    - MIX_ADD (1): Additive mix mode.

GDScript:
```gdscript
var anim_node = AnimationNodeOneShot.new()
anim_node.animation = "jump"
anim_node.delay = 0.2
anim_node.fade_out = 0.1
```

C#:
```csharp
var animNode = new AnimationNodeOneShot();
animNode.Animation = "jump";
animNode.Delay = 0.2f;
animNode.FadeOut = 0.1f;
```
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for the AnimationNodeOneShot class, controlling its behavior for playing animations once.

Properties:
- abort_on_reset (bool): If true, the one-shot animation will be aborted if the node is reset. Default: false.
- autorestart (bool): If true, the one-shot animation will restart automatically after it finishes. Default: false.
- autorestart_delay (float): The delay in seconds before the animation restarts if autorestart is true. Default: 1.0.
- autorestart_random_delay (float): A random delay in seconds to add to the autorestart_delay. Default: 0.0.
- break_loop_at_end (bool): If true, and the animation is a loop, it will be broken at the end of the one-shot playback. Default: false.
- fadein_curve (Curve): The curve used to control the fade-in transition.
- fadein_time (float): The duration of the fade-in transition in seconds. Default: 0.0.
- fadeout_curve (Curve): The curve used to control the fade-out transition.
- fadeout_time (float): The duration of the fade-out transition in seconds. Default: 0.0.
- mix_mode (MixMode): The mode used for mixing the animation when it's not playing. Default: 0.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: Defines enumerations for controlling the behavior and mixing modes of the AnimationNodeOneShot.

Enumerations
enum OneShotRequest:
  ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_NONE = 0
    The default state of the request. Nothing is done.
  ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FIRE = 1
    The request to play the animation connected to "shot" port.
  ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_ABORT = 2
    The request to stop the animation connected to "shot" port.
  ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FADE_OUT = 3
    The request to fade out the animation connected to "shot" port.

enum MixMode:
  MIX_MODE_BLEND = 0
    Blends two animations. See also AnimationNodeBlend2.
  MIX_MODE_ADD = 1
    Blends two animations additively. See also AnimationNodeAdd2.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeOneShot
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeoneshot.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the AnimationNodeOneShot, including fade settings, autorestart behavior, and mixing modes.

Property: abort_on_reset (bool). Default: false.
Method: set_abort_on_reset(value: bool) → void
Method: is_aborted_on_reset() → bool
If true, the sub-animation will abort if resumed with a reset after a prior interruption.

Property: autorestart (bool). Default: false.
Method: set_autorestart(value: bool) → void
Method: has_autorestart() → bool
If true, the sub-animation will restart automatically after finishing. To start auto restarting, the animation must be played once with the ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FIRE request. The ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_ABORT request stops the auto restarting, but it does not disable the autorestart property itself. The ONE_SHOT_REQUEST_FIRE request will start auto restarting again.

Property: autorestart_delay (float). Default: 1.0.
Method: set_autorestart_delay(value: float) → void
Method: get_autorestart_delay() → float
The delay after which the automatic restart is triggered, in seconds.

Property: autorestart_random_delay (float). Default: 0.0.
Method: set_autorestart_random_delay(value: float) → void
Method: get_autorestart_random_delay() → float
If autorestart is true, a random additional delay (in seconds) between 0 and this value will be added to autorestart_delay.

Property: break_loop_at_end (bool). Default: false.
Method: set_break_loop_at_end(value: bool) → void
Method: is_loop_broken_at_end() → bool
If true, breaks the loop at the end of the loop cycle for transition, even if the animation is looping.

Property: fadein_curve (Curve).
Method: set_fadein_curve(value: Curve) → void
Method: get_fadein_curve() → Curve
Determines how cross-fading between animations is eased. If empty, the transition will be linear. Should be a unit Curve.

Property: fadein_time (float). Default: 0.0.
Method: set_fadein_time(value: float) → void
Method: get_fadein_time() → float
The fade-in duration. For example, setting this to 1.0 for a 5 second length animation will produce a cross-fade that starts at 0 second and ends at 1 second during the animation. Note: AnimationNodeOneShot transitions the current state after the fading has finished.

Property: fadeout_curve (Curve).
Method: set_fadeout_curve(value: Curve) → void
Method: get_fadeout_curve() → Curve
Determines how cross-fading between animations is eased. If empty, the transition will be linear. Should be a unit Curve.

Property: fadeout_time (float). Default: 0.0.
Method: set_fadeout_time(value: float) → void
Method: get_fadeout_time() → float
The fade-out duration. For example, setting this to 1.0 for a 5 second length animation will produce a cross-fade that starts at 4 second and ends at 5 second during the animation. Note: AnimationNodeOneShot transitions the current state after the fading has finished.

Property: mix_mode (MixMode). Default: 0.
Method: set_mix_mode(value: MixMode) → void
Method: get_mix_mode() → MixMode
The blend type.